<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="proper-adj">proper <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'prɒpə(r)/    美 /'prɑːpər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>适当的；恰当的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>People today spend much time seeking the <strong>proper way</strong> to raise children. 
如今，人们花很多时间寻求恰当的育儿方法。</p><footer>2008 福建</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He wore proper clothes for the party.
他穿着得体，参加了聚会。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>合乎体统的</strong></h4>
<p>反 improper ： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His mother has trained him to be a very proper young man. 
他的母亲已经把他训练成一个举止得体的年轻人。</p></div></div>